{"id": "software-development--mesh-utility-org", "title": "mesh-utility.org", "forum": "software-development", "messages": [{"id": "1470371781691965685", "author": "Just Stuff™", "author_handle": "just_stuff_tm", "user_id": "1282595699300630593", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/1282595699300630593/c9f05211fb1890bb2718d91541c2c1cd.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, February 9, 2026 5:52 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-09 5:52 a.m.", "text": "It just works! https://mesh-utility.org What Is Mesh Utility? Mesh Utility is a free tool that helps you see how well your LoRa mesh radio network covers an area. Walk or drive around with your radio connected, and the app builds a color-coded map showing where your signal is strong, weak, or missing entirely. Currently only supports Meshcore ble companion firmware. 8 languages: English, Spanish, French, German, Portuguese, Chinese, Japanese, and Korean Optional offline capabilities. Vite React Rolling updates. (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>It just works!\n<a href=\"https://mesh-utility.org\">https://mesh-utility.org</a>\n\n\nWhat Is Mesh Utility?\n\nMesh Utility is a free tool that helps you see how well your LoRa mesh radio network covers an area. Walk or drive around with your radio connected, and the app builds a color-coded map showing where your signal is strong, weak, or missing entirely.\n\nCurrently only supports Meshcore ble companion firmware.\n\n8 languages: English, Spanish, French, German, Portuguese, Chinese, Japanese, and Korean\n\n\nOptional offline capabilities.\n\nVite React\n\nRolling updates.</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Wednesday, February 18, 2026 2:38 p.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": ["<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=\"chatlog__embed-color-pill chatlog__embed-color-pill--default\"></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-conte